  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving the Disadvantaged Farm Households&apos; Capacity in Tra Vinh Province through VBHCD</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is a joint effort of Heifer Vietnam and Tra Vinh Veterinary Department to assist poor communities in Cang Long District to develop holistically by applying Heifer&#x2019;s Value-Based Holistic Community Development (VBHCD) model. The project will provide 125 heifers, 50 pigs and a micro-credit fund of $112 per family to 150 families. In addition to animal distribution, participants will receive trainings on Heifer&#x2019;s 12 Cornerstones, self-help group management, technical and non-technical issues. Another 175 families will benefit from Passing on the Gift of training, animals and the micro-credit fund.</narrative>
  </description>
